    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="429"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/319: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-15T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 15, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. Referring exchange of notes between Embassy and Chilean Foreign Office,
                    Embassy [<hi rend="italic">dated?</hi>] February 1, 1938,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d429fn2">Department of State Executive Agreement Series No. 119, or
                        52 Stat. 1479.</note> pursuant to Department’s telegram No. 13, February 4,
                    4 p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d429fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1938v05#pg_430">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1938, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 430</ref>.</note> regarding provisional
                    duration of <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> of January 6, 1938,<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d429fn4">For text, see Executive Agreement Series No. 119, or 52
                        Stat. 1479.</note> I have the honor to report that as Chilean Congress has
                    not ratified <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> the latter lapsed on January
                    31, 1939. Foreign Office entirely agreeable that it be promptly signed again, as
                    of February 1, 1939, in accordance with concluding sentence of the notes of
                    February 1, 1938 cited above. Suggest instruction authorizing this at early
                    date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
